---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service">
    <div class="py-24 bg-white">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 font-serif mb-8">
                Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
                    Last updated: February 16, 2026
                </p>

                <h2
                    class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 font-serif"
                >
                    1. Acceptance of Terms
                </h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                    By accessing or using LienSign, you agree to be bound by
                    these Terms of Service.
                </p>

                <h2
                    class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 font-serif"
                >
                    2. No Legal Advice Disclaimer
                </h2>
                <p
                    class="bg-blue-50 p-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 text-slate-800 font-medium mb-4"
                >
                    LienSign is a software tool for generating
                    construction-related documents. LienSign is NOT a law firm
                    and does NOT provide legal advice. The use of our templates
                    or services does not create an attorney-client relationship.
                    You should consult with a qualified attorney for legal
                    matters.
                </p>

                <h2
                    class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 font-serif"
                >
                    3. Description of Service
                </h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                    LienSign provides a local-first browser tool to help
                    construction professionals generate lien waivers based on
                    user-provided data. All processing happens locally on your
                    device.
                </p>

                <h2
                    class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 font-serif"
                >
                    4. User Responsibilities
                </h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                    You are responsible for the accuracy of the information
                    provided. Since data is stored locally on your device, you
                    are also responsible for maintaining copies of your
                    generated documents.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
